18. Quantam, &c Here the whole plot is unravelled, and every thing prepared for the happy conclusion of the play. By the manage- ment of the poet, Bacchis is left alone upon the stage, where she informs the spectators how she came to make this important discovery, which removes every obstacle, and reconciles the several disagreeing parties. — 20.
